  "why": "Although CrossASR++ runs inputs across multiple ASR systems simultaneously (differential testing) and reports failures per system, the paper does not perform or report experiments that take fault-inducing inputs discovered on one model and reuse them to test other, independently-trained target models (the required reuse to demonstrate attack transferability). The evaluation shows benefits of adding more ASRs for cross-referencing (more failures found), but there is no explicit mechanism to craft transferable attacks nor any experiment that demonstrates reusing failures discovered on a surrogate to cause failures on an unseen target.",
